title: Ask HN: Spreading risk as early stage tech co-founder
text:
I’m considering helping non-tech co-founders with their idea. The ones I have spoken to are pre-funding. I’d likely be architecting and building MVP/version 1.

I’d be working at this full time so would be looking for a wage within a year - what is the best way to hedge my bets pre-funding? Work with two 20hrs/week each? Or work on one at a time and look to fail fast within a couple months?

I don’t want to burn my co-founder relationship by suggesting something that is uncommon.

Ask HN: Anyone based in EU remotely contracting with US clients?
text:
Has anyone managed to get into contracting with US clients while being physically based in EU?

1. I think contracting should be easier than employing wrt bureaucracy and other regulations (e.g. no visas and the likes).

2. Timezone might be an issue?

3. What about rates? I guess US companies would prefer US contractors when they have the same rate as EU contractors?
